Me and my 3 babies are barely surviving.. everyday it's a struggle for me to provide and I am from a reserve in Ontario .. yes i worked in the past then my rare medicle condition took over, n it gets hard to do so, i am only 27 years old and spent most of my life in hospitals all over ontario and manitoba, i am in and out of a wheelchair still caring for my 3 babies alone as a single mother (ages between 12 months and 5 years old) I am declined disability because my medicle condition is to rare, work is very limited here, let me tell you.. me and my 3 kids get 150 every two weeks to live.. that's 300 a month. For utilities, food, my child's needs, ect..( I do not get their child tax because of someone who I had filing my taxes wrong) and because of that mistake I owe the government over 26,000 dollars.. some medicle care are not covered and owe alot in medicle bills for me and my kids because ontario Dr's refuse to take us so we drive to Manitoba for each appointment because my medicle condition is to rare and my children had to be born in Manitoba because of it. (even then it's a struggle). . Theres not much programs here and if there is other people ruin them for others and can no longer be used... it's very hard and almost survivinh indeed
